- task_model_Python.prompt
- storage_Python.prompt

Instructions
- Import argparse, sys from standard library, and storage module functions (add_task, load_tasks, complete_task, delete_task)
- Create ArgumentParser with description='Simple command-line todo list application'
- Add subparsers with subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest='command', required=True)
- Define add subcommand: parser_add = subparsers.add_parser('add', help='Add a new task'); parser_add.add_argument('description', type=str, help='Task description'); parser_add.set_defaults(func=handle_add)
- Define list subcommand: parser_list = subparsers.add_parser('list', help='List all tasks'); parser_list.set_defaults(func=handle_list)
- Define complete subcommand: parser_complete = subparsers.add_parser('complete', help='Mark a task as completed'); parser_complete.add_argument('task_id', type=int, help='Task ID'); parser_complete.set_defaults(func=handle_complete)
- Define delete subcommand: parser_delete = subparsers.add_parser('delete', help='Delete a task'); parser_delete.add_argument('task_id', type=int, help='Task ID'); parser_delete.set_defaults(func=handle_delete)
- Implement handle_add(args) that calls storage.add_task(args.description) and prints "Added task {task.id}: {task.description}"
- Implement handle_list(args) that calls storage.load_tasks() and prints each task formatted as "{task.id}. [{'✓' if task.completed else ' '}] {task.description} (created: {task.created_at.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')})"
- Implement handle_complete(args) that calls storage.complete_task(args.task_id) and prints success or "Task {task_id} not found" based on return value
- Implement handle_delete(args) that calls storage.delete_task(args.task_id) and prints success or "Task {task_id} not found" based on return value
- Implement main() function that parses args, calls args.func(args), and wraps in try-except to catch storage exceptions and print to stderr before exiting with code 1
- Use sys.exit(1) for error exits, sys.exit(0) or implicit return for success
- Print error messages to sys.stderr using print(..., file=sys.stderr)
- Handle empty task list in handle_list by printing "No tasks found." instead of empty output

Deliverable
- A single Python file todo.py containing the main() function and all command handlers
- The file should be executable as a script: python todo.py <command> [args]
- Clean, user-friendly output format for all operations
- Proper error handling with informative messages for common failure cases

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- Script runs in same directory as todos.json or user provides full path (not implemented in this version)
- Python 3.9+ for type hints (list[Task] syntax)
- Terminal supports Unicode characters for checkmarks (✓)
- No color output or advanced formatting (keep it simple for v1)
- No configuration file or environment variables needed

Please produce production-ready code for the CLI module consistent with the above requirements.
